<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910424-0081</DOCNO><DOCID>910424-0081.</DOCID><HL>   Loss at Consolidated   Freightways Shrank   In the First Quarter</HL><DATE>04/24/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   CNF</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)COMMERCIAL TRUCKING AND RELATED WAREHOUSING (TRK)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)</RE><LP>   MENLO PARK, Calif. -- Consolidated Freightways Inc. saidthe recession hurt all aspects of its shipping and freightbusiness, resulting in a first-quarter loss.   The freight-trucking and shipping company reported a lossof $14.3 million, or 41 cents a share. It was something of arecovery when compared with a loss of $37.1 million, or $1.06a share, a year ago, but the latest loss was greater thanmost analysts' expectations of roughly 30 cents a share.Revenue rose almost 5% to $1.05 billion from $997.7 million.</LP><TEXT>   Analysts say there are tentative signs of a rebound forthe company, which is plagued mainly by losses from its EmeryWorldwide air-freight and overnight express service,purchased for $470 million in debt assumption and cash in1989.   &quot;The bright side is that things no longer appear to be outof control on the down side, with regard to Emery,&quot; said PaulSchlesinger, an analyst with Alex Brown. &quot;They're makingprogress. It's a question of whether or not they makeenough.&quot;   Emery Worldwide cut its losses to $18.4 million from $69.5million for the first quarter a year ago, and increasedrevenue 20% to $382.3 million from $317.8 million a year ago.Last week the unit announced it would reduce its work force9.6%, terminating about 1,000 of its 10,400 employees. Theunit was boosted by the renewal of a U.S. Postal contract tocarry express priority mail.   CF Motor Frieght, the company's long-haul trucking unit,reported a 56% drop in operating profit to $9.5 million from$21.6 million a year ago. Revenue fell 1% to $519.4 from$523.1 million.   The company's regional carrier, ConWay TransportationServices, had a 5% decline in operating profit to $7.4million from $7.8 million. Revenue fell 8% to $144.7 millionfrom $156.7 million.</TEXT></DOC>